uk.blankaspect.common.indexedsub

Class IndexedSub

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.blankaspect.common.indexedsub.IndexedSub

  • public class IndexedSub
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides methods that substitute replacement sequences for occurrences of placeholders in a string. A placeholder has the form "%n", where n is a decimal string representation of an integer greater than or equal to 1.

    • Method Detail

      • sub

        public static java.lang.String sub(java.lang.String str,
                                   java.lang.CharSequence... replacements)
        Substitutes the specified replacement sequences for occurrences of placeholders in the specified string, and returns the resulting string. A placeholder has the form "%n", where n is a decimal string representation of an integer greater than or equal to 1. Each placeholder is replaced by the specified sequence whose zero-based index is n-1; for example, the placeholder "%3" will be replaced by the sequence at index 2. A placeholder that does not have a corresponding replacement sequence is replaced by an empty string.

        If a literal "%" is required in the output string, it must be escaped by prefixing another "%" to it (ie, "%%"). An unescaped "%" will be replaced by an empty string.

        Parameters:
        str - the string on which substitutions will be performed.
        replacements - the sequences that will replace placeholders in str.
        Returns:
        a transformation of the input string in which each placeholder is replaced by the element of replacements at the corresponding index.

      • sub

        public static java.lang.String sub(java.lang.String str,
                                   int... replacementValues)
        Substitutes the decimal string representations of the specified integer values for occurrences of placeholders in the specified string, and returns the resulting string. A placeholder has the form "%n", where n is a decimal string representation of an integer greater than or equal to 1. Each placeholder is replaced by the string representation of the specified value whose zero-based index is n-1; for example, the placeholder "%3" will be replaced by the string representation of the value at index 2. A placeholder that does not have a corresponding replacement value is replaced by an empty string.

        If a literal "%" is required in the output string, it must be escaped by prefixing another "%" to it (ie, "%%"). An unescaped "%" will be replaced by an empty string.

        Parameters:
        str - the string on which substitutions will be performed.
        replacementValues - the values whose decimal string representations will replace placeholders in str.
        Returns:
        a transformation of the input string in which each placeholder is replaced by the the decimal string representation of the element of replacementValues at the corresponding index.
